fastapi0.110.0
The web server that runs your ML service. Node.js sends it a transaction, it runs the ML model, it sends back a fraud score. Think of it as Express.js — but in Python.
In your app: POST /fraud/score, POST /anomaly/check, GET /health

server
uvicorn0.29.0
The engine that actually runs FastAPI. FastAPI is the framework, uvicorn is the runner — like how Express needs Node to run. You never call it directly, it just powers everything.
In your app: python main.py → uvicorn starts listening on port 8000

