The Swiss army knife of ML. Has Random Forest (used in your fraud model), train/test split, accuracy scoring. The most beginner-friendly ML library — most tutorials use this.
In your app: RandomForestClassifier for fraud detection, SMOTE helper

ML model
xgboost2.0.3
A very powerful, fast ML algorithm. Wins most Kaggle competitions. Better than Random Forest for fraud detection because it handles imbalanced data (only 3.5% of transactions are fraud) well.
In your app: fraud detection model, loan default risk model

ML model
lightgbm4.2.0
Similar to XGBoost but faster and uses less memory. Works great with SHAP for explaining WHY a score was given ("your utilization is 85%, that's hurting your score").
In your app: credit score simulator — shows which factors affect the score

ML model
tensorflow2.15.0
Google's deep learning library. Used for neural networks — more complex than XGBoost but needed for patterns that change over time (like your spending habits month by month).
In your app: LSTM for expense prediction, Autoencoder for anomaly detection

ML model
imbalanced-learn0.12.0
Solves a real problem: in your fraud data, only 3.5% of rows are actual fraud. If you train on that, the model just says "not fraud" every time and is 96.5% accurate — but useless. This library fakes extra fraud examples so the model actually learns.
In your app: SMOTE — generates synthetic fraud transactions for training

ML model
shap0.44.1
SHAP = SHapley Additive exPlanations. Makes black-box ML models explainable. Instead of just saying "credit score: 620", it tells you exactly which factors helped or hurt the score and by how much.
In your app: credit simulator shows { utilization: -30pts, payment_history: +15pts }



